webpackJsonp([42791245891822],{357:function(a,s){a.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>A CSS selector is like patterns which are used to select and style the pattern matching elements. We will compare <code class="language-text">CSS3</code> with <code class="language-text">CSS4</code> selectors and give some examples for better understanding.</p>\n<h2>Pseudo Class</h2>\n<p>Pseudo class in CSS is used to defined a special state of an element. Such as visited links have the state of <code class="language-text">:visited</code>.</p>\n<h2>CSS3</h2>\n<h3>:not()</h3>\n<p><code class="language-text">:not</code> pseudo class selector is used to select all the elements except the one which is specified in the argument.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="html">\n      <pre class="language-html"><code class="language-html"><span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class="token attr-name">href</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>/<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span> <span class="token attr-name">class</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>link<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Link 1<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class="token attr-name">href</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>No Link<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class="token attr-name">href</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span></span> <span class="token attr-name">rel</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>nofollow<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>No Follow<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class="token attr-name">href</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>/<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span> <span class="token attr-name">class</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>link<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Link 2<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>We have 4 <code class="language-text">&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</code> tags, two with a class <code class="language-text">link</code> and one with <code class="language-text">rel</code> attribute and one normal link.</p>\n<p>So lets set the color of all the anchor tags to <span class="color__red"><code class="language-text">red</code></span> expect the one’s which has class <code class="language-text">.link</code>.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="css">\n      <pre class="language-css"><code class="language-css"><span class="token selector">a:not(.link)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token property">color</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> red<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3>Example:</h3>\n<p data-height="265" data-theme-id="dark" data-slug-hash="NdmWWz" data-default-tab="html,result" data-user="gokulkrishh" data-embed-version="2" data-pen-title="CSS3 :not selector" class="codepen">See the Pen <a href="http://codepen.io/gokulkrishh/pen/NdmWWz/">CSS3 :not selector</a> by Gokulakrishnan Kalaikovan (<a href="http://codepen.io/gokulkrishh">@gokulkrishh</a>) on <a href="http://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.</p>\n<p>In above example, I don’t want to set the color to <span class="color__red"><code class="language-text">red</code></span> for <code class="language-text">rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;</code>. But <code class="language-text">CSS3</code> :not() selector allows only one argument.</p>\n<p>Now let us see in <b>CSS4</b>.</p>\n<h2>CSS4</h2>\n<h3>:not()</h3>\n<p>Allows setting multiple arguments for the <code class="language-text">:not(selector1, selector2)</code> pseudo class selector.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="css">\n      <pre class="language-css"><code class="language-css"><span class="token selector">a:not(.link, [rel="nofollow"])</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token property">color</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> red<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>The above example will let me to set the color of <code class="language-text">&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</code> tags to <span class="color__red"><code class="language-text">red</code></span> which doesn’t have <code class="language-text">.link</code> class and <code class="language-text">rel=nofollow</code> attribute.</p>\n<h3>:matches()</h3>\n<p>Takes multiple arguments and represents an element which is specified in the argument.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="html">\n      <pre class="language-html"><code class="language-html"><span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>header</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n  <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Header Title<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>header</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>General Title<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class="token attr-name">class</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>container<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n  <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Container Title<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>section</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n  <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Section Title<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>section</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Now I want to change the color of some <code class="language-text">&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code> tags to <span class="color__green"><code class="language-text">green</code></span>. Normally we write it likes.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="css">\n      <pre class="language-css"><code class="language-css"><span class="token selector">&lt;!-- Normal Way -->\nheader h1, .container h1</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token property">color</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> green<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\n<span class="token selector">&lt;!-- CSS4 -->\n:matches(header, .container) h1</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token property">color</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> green<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3>List of some CSS4 selectors.</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Selectors</th>\n<th align="left">Does</th>\n<th align="right">CSS</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#negation">\n:not(s1, s2, s3)\n</a></td>\n<td align="left">Allows multiple arguments</td>\n<td align="right">3/4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#matches">\n:match(s1, s2)\n</a></td>\n<td align="left">Matches the elements specified in the arugment</td>\n<td align="right">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#attribute-case">\na[href=home i]\n</a></td>\n<td align="left">Case Insensitive (home, HOME, Home etc,.)</td>\n<td align="right">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#any-link-pseudo">\n:any-link\n</a></td>\n<td align="left">Matches source of hyperlink (a, link etc,.)</td>\n<td align="right">4</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>Browser Support:</h3>\n<p>Only <code class="language-text">38%</code> of CSS4 selectors are supported by the browsers.</p>\n\n  <a class="gatsby-resp-image-link" href="/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-03179.png" style="display: block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">\n  \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 69.49654491609081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="CSS4 Support" title="" src="/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-fb8a0.png" srcset="/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-526de.png 885w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-08f6a.png 1770w,\n/static/css4-support-639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc-03179.png 2026w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n<center><i>Source <a href="http://css4-selectors.com/browser-selector-test/" target="_blank">Browser Selector Test</a></i></center>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>There are close to 22 new CSS level 4 selectors. Some of them are really cool and let us write less CSS code. But like mentioned above not all the browsers supports the level 4 selectors. Thanks for reading and see you in my next blog post. If you like my post, share it or comment below.</p>\n<h4>Articles</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4" target="_blank">Full list of CSS4 selectors</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://css4.rocks/" target="_blank">CSS4 Rocks</a></li>\n</ul>\n<script async src="https://production-assets.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js"></script>\n<p> Thanks for reading my blog post 😁</p>',frontmatter:{date:"February 28, 2016",path:"/blog/2016/css4-selectors",title:"CSS4 Selectors"}}},pathContext:{}}}});